<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="28" pageNumber="59">Type locality. Southern coast of eastern United States.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="28" pageNumber="59">Distribution. Black Sea Basin, Caspian Sea, coasts of western Europe, Caribbean, and northern South America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="28" pageNumber="59">
Remarks. The species, native to the southern coast of North America, was first introduced in Europe in 1835 (
<bibRefCitation author="Heiler, KCM" journalOrPublisher="Malacologia" pageId="76" pageNumber="107" pagination="185 - 192" title="A New Invasion Into an Ancient Lake - The Invasion History of the Dreissenid Mussel Mytilopsisleucophaeata (Conrad, 1831) and Its First Record in the Caspian Sea." url="https://doi.org/10.4002/040.053.0112" volume="53" year="2010">Heiler et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). In the Pontocaspian region, it first 
<pageBreakToken pageId="29" pageNumber="60" start="start">appeared</pageBreakToken>
in the northern Black Sea Basin in 2002 and was first collected in the Caspian Sea in 2009 (
<bibRefCitation author="Heiler, KCM" journalOrPublisher="Malacologia" pageId="76" pageNumber="107" pagination="185 - 192" title="A New Invasion Into an Ancient Lake - The Invasion History of the Dreissenid Mussel Mytilopsisleucophaeata (Conrad, 1831) and Its First Record in the Caspian Sea." url="https://doi.org/10.4002/040.053.0112" volume="53" year="2010">Heiler et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). It is easily distinguished from Pontocaspian dreissenids by the presence of an aphophysis near the hinge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="conservation">
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="60">
Conservation status. Least Concern (
<bibRefCitation author="Cummings, K" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="73" pageNumber="104" url="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2011-2.RLTS.T155623A4809971.en" year="2011">Cummings 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
